What is Greedy Algorithm (from zero)

ğŸ‘‰ Greedy = take the best option right now, hoping it leads to the final best answer.

You donâ€™t think about future

You donâ€™t try all possibilities

You decide step by step, locally best choice

ğŸ“Œ One-line definition for exams

A Greedy algorithm makes the locally optimal choice at each step to reach a globally optimal solution.

âœ… Use GREEDY when:

Local best choice always leads to global best

Once you make a choice, you never regret it

The problem says:

maximum profit

minimum time

earliest finish

largest value first

Sorting + one pass works

ğŸ“Œ Examples:

Activity Selection

Fractional Knapsack

Minimum platforms

Huffman coding

âŒ Greedy FAILS when:

Two or more smaller choices together beat one big choice

Current decision affects future options

You need to try all combinations

â¡ï¸ This is where DP comes in.

